Micropolis Corp is raising 75 mln dlrsvia an offering of convertible subordinated debentures due 2012with a six pct coupon and par pricing, said lead managerKidder, Peabody and Co Inc.    The debentures are convertible into the company's commonstock at 48.50 dlrs per share, representing a premium of 23.6pct over the stock price when terms on the debt were set.    Non-callable for two years, the issue is rated B-minus byStandard and Poor's. Robertson, Colman and Stephens co-managedthe deal. Reuter&#3;